		<description>This scenario puts a fleet of Sopwith Camels, SPAD VIIs, and Fokker Triplanes in the skies over Marin County, starting at the Marin Ranch Airport, CA35.

If you take off from runway 22 of the Marin Ranch Airport (CA35), the planes will be directly above you and around the airport as you take off, headed in a westerly direction.  

The planes have no contrails or other traces and are very, very difficult to pick out from the background clutter.

As soon as you are in the air, pause FG and look around your horizon and above you.  You may need to zoom in and examine the hills closely. You will find several Camels.  Choose one as your target and dogfight through the hills.  

You can then do file/reset to bring yourself and all the planes back to Marin Ranch, where you can pick another target and try again.

The Camels, SPADs, and Triplanes are air-to-air targets, you can damage them with heavy guns, machine guns, or (if you can hit them!) heavy bombs.
  
When you shoot or bomb the Camels they will catch fire, slow down, fall, and finally crash (to see the smoke and fire you must have Particles enabled in View/Rendering Options).

To damage the aircraft takes one or more direct hits from a machine gun or heavy gun, or a close strike by a heavy bomb.   The Camels are fairly easy targets for heavy guns or bombs, less so for light bombs--similar to a Cessna C172 in difficulty to kill.

Install this scenario in the FlightGear/data/AI directory.

Any aircraft that shoots guns or drops bombs can damage the Camels, SPADs, and Triplanes.  A great choice is to use the Sopwith Camel aircraft included in this distribution, which has working machine guns and several other improvements/fixes over the current CVS version of the Sopwith.
		</description>
		
